76 // Update the inputs of {phi} so that they all have {repr} representation, and
77 // updates {phi}'s representation to {repr}.
78 void ConvertTaggedPhiTo(Phi* phi, ValueRepresentation repr,
79 const HoistTypeList& hoist_untagging);
80
81 // Since this pass changes the representation of Phis, it makes some untagging
82 // operations outdated: if we've decided that a Phi should have Int32
83 // representation, then we don't need to do a kCheckedSmiUntag before using
84 // it. UpdateNodeInputs(n) removes such untagging from {n}'s input (and insert
85 // new conversions if needed, from Int32 to Float64 for instance).
86 template <class NodeT>
87 ProcessResult UpdateNodeInputs(NodeT* n, const ProcessingState& state) {
88 NodeBase* node = static_cast<NodeBase*>(n);
89
90 ProcessResult result = ProcessResult::kContinue;
91 if (IsUntagging(n->opcode())) {
92 if (node->input(0).node()->Is<Phi>() &&
93 node->input(0).node()->value_representation() !=
94 ValueRepresentation::kTagged) {
95 DCHECK_EQ(node->input_count(), 1);
96 // This untagging conversion is outdated, since its input has been
97 // untagged. Depending on the conversion, it might need to be replaced
98 // by another untagged->untagged conversion, or it might need to be
99 // removed alltogether (or rather, replaced by an identity node).
100 UpdateUntaggingOfPhi(node->input(0).node()->Cast<Phi>(),
101 n->template Cast<ValueNode>());
102 }
103 } else {
104 result = UpdateNonUntaggingNodeInputs(n, state);
105 }
106
107 // It's important to check the properties of {node} rather than the static
108 // properties of `NodeT`, because `UpdateUntaggingOfPhi` could have changed
109 // the opcode of {node}, potentially converting a deopting node into a
110 // non-deopting one.
111 if (node->properties().can_eager_deopt()) {
112 BypassIdentities(node->eager_deopt_info());
113 }
114 if (node->properties().can_lazy_deopt()) {
115 BypassIdentities(node->lazy_deopt_info());
116 }
117
118 return result;
119 }
120
121 template <class NodeT>
122 ProcessResult UpdateNonUntaggingNodeInputs(NodeT* n,
123 const ProcessingState& state) {
124 NodeBase* node = static_cast<NodeBase*>(n);
125
126 // It would be bad to re-tag the input of an untagging node, so this
127 // function should never be called on untagging nodes.
128 DCHECK(!IsUntagging(n->opcode()));
129
130 for (int i = 0; i < n->input_count(); i++) {
131 ValueNode* input = node->input(i).node();
132 if (input->Is<Identity>()) {
133 // Bypassing the identity
134 node->change_input(i, input->input(0).node());
135 } else if (Phi* phi = input->TryCast<Phi>()) {
136 // If the input is a Phi and it was used without any untagging, then
137 // we need to retag it (with some additional checks/changes for some
138 // nodes, cf the overload of UpdateNodePhiInput).
139 ProcessResult result = UpdateNodePhiInput(n, phi, i, state);
140 if (V8_UNLIKELY(result == ProcessResult::kRemove)) {
141 return ProcessResult::kRemove;
142 }
143 }
144 }
145
146 return ProcessResult::kContinue;
147 }

174 // NewNodePosition is used to represent where a new node should be inserted:
175 // at the start of a block (kStart), or at the end of a block (kEnd).
176 enum class NewNodePosition { kStart, kEnd };
177
178 // Returns a tagged node that represents a tagged version of {phi}.
179 // If we are calling EnsurePhiTagged to ensure a Phi input of a Phi is tagged,
180 // then {predecessor_index} should be set to the id of this input (ie, 0 for
181 // the 1st input, 1 for the 2nd, etc.), so that we can use the SnapshotTable
182 // to find existing tagging for {phi} in the {predecessor_index}th predecessor
183 // of the current block.
184 ValueNode* EnsurePhiTagged(
185 Phi* phi, BasicBlock* block, NewNodePosition pos,
186 base::Optional<int> predecessor_index = base::nullopt);
187
188 ValueNode* AddNode(ValueNode* node, BasicBlock* block, NewNodePosition pos,
189 DeoptFrame* deopt_frame = nullptr);
190 void RegisterNewNode(ValueNode* node);
191
192 // Merges the nodes from {new_nodes_current_block_start_} and
193 // {new_nodes_current_block_end_} into their destinations.
194 void MergeNewNodesInBlock(BasicBlock* block);
195
196 // If {block} is the start of a loop header, FixLoopPhisBackedge inserts the
197 // necessary tagging on the backedge of the loop Phis of the loop header.
198 // Additionally, if {block} contains untagged loop phis whose backedges have
199 // been updated to Identity, FixLoopPhisBackedge unwraps those Identity.
200 void FixLoopPhisBackedge(BasicBlock* block);
201
202 // Replaces Identity nodes by their inputs in {deopt_info}
203 template <typename DeoptInfoT>
204 void BypassIdentities(DeoptInfoT* deopt_info);
205
206 void PreparePhiTaggings(BasicBlock* old_block, const BasicBlock* new_block);
207
208 MaglevGraphLabeller* graph_labeller() const {
209 return builder_->graph_labeller();
210 }
211
212 bool CanHoistUntaggingTo(BasicBlock* block);
213
214 MaglevGraphBuilder* builder_ = nullptr;
215 BasicBlock* current_block_ = nullptr;
216
217 // {new_nodes_current_block_start_}, {new_nodes_current_block_end_} and
218 // are used to store new nodes added by this pass, but to delay their
219 // insertion into their destination, in order to not mutate the linked list of
220 // nodes of the current block while also iterating it. Nodes in
221 // {new_nodes_current_block_start_} and {new_nodes_current_block_end_} will be
222 // inserted respectively at the begining and the end of the current block.
223 ZoneVector<Node*> new_nodes_current_block_start_;
224 ZoneVector<Node*> new_nodes_current_block_end_;
225
226 // {phi_taggings_} is a SnapshotTable containing mappings from untagged Phis
227 // to Tagged alternatives for those phis.
228 SnapshotTable<ValueNode*> phi_taggings_;
229 // {predecessors_} is used during merging, but we use an instance variable for
230 // it, in order to save memory and not reallocate it for each merge.
231 ZoneVector<Snapshot> predecessors_;
232
233#ifdef DEBUG
234 std::unordered_set<NodeBase*> new_nodes_;
235#endif
236};
